     1|/**
     2| * IVX Self-Hosted Senior Developer Worker — removes the Rork dependency as the
     3| * code EXECUTOR.
     4| *
     5| * Rork is no longer required to run a development task. Instead:
     6| *   1. IVX IA (or the owner-gated API) submits an owner-approved task to this
     7| *      worker's durable job QUEUE.
     8| *   2. A single-flight WORKER drains the queue and runs the real end-to-end
     9| *      execution pipeline already implemented in `ivx-senior-developer-runtime`:
    10| *      repo read → file create/modify → tests → typecheck → build → commit →
    11| *      push → Render deploy → poll deploy → verify /health + /version.
    12| *   3. Every job's verifiable result is recorded in a durable PROOF LEDGER
    13| *      (Supabase-backed, survives Render's diskless restarts; in-memory fallback
    14| *      for local/test).
    15| *
    16| * This module owns ONLY the orchestration that did not exist before (queue,
    17| * worker loop, ledger). It reuses the proven execution primitives so there is
    18| * no duplicated GitHub/Render/test logic and no fabricated proof.
    19| *
    20| * Security:
    21| *   - Owner approval is enforced at the API boundary BEFORE a job is enqueued;
    22| *     the approval contract is stored on the job. The worker refuses to run a
    23| *     job whose `ownerApproved` flag is not true.
    24| *   - No secret values are ever stored on a job or in the ledger.
    25| */
